<subSubSection id="28CD4E7B6E20BF37087B69FDEBC0DED3" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="1EA8C20B5597E774F68AC01A3D5C1631" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DC5329FB8B1B048365889B51DEEAD79E" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="F5A2FDA38021628E18330297BDF2DA02" authority="Terayama, 2004" authorityName="Terayama" authorityYear="2004" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Formosiepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Formosiepyris marishi" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marishi">Formosiepyris marishi</taxonomicName>
based on the convex posterior margin of the head in full-face view; having a punctated pronotum with microreticulate interspaces; punctures on pronotum sparser than those on head; and absence of longitudinal striae on propodeum surface between median carina and inner submedian carina. However, this species can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="D8204368538D4A7BE03F9C9ADA7523E4" authority="Terayama, 2004" authorityName="Terayama" authorityYear="2004" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Formosiepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Formosiepyris marishi" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marishi">Formosiepyris marishi</taxonomicName>
by having a weakly rounded anterior margin of the clypeus; head wider than long; ocelli forming an obtuse triangle; second antennomere shorter than third antennomere; and second and third tergites with small sparsely located punctures and smooth interspaces, except for microreticulated anterior 2/5.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
